# Markdown Linking Standards

## Always Use Relative Paths

All internal documentation links must use relative paths, never absolute paths.

## Link Path Patterns

### From Root README

When linking from [README.md](mdc:README.md) to documentation:

```markdown
✅ CORRECT:
[ARCHITECTURE-FLOWS.md](./docs/architecture/ARCHITECTURE-FLOWS.md)
[BOT-SETUP.md](./docs/archive/BOT-SETUP.md)
[MONITORING-GUIDE.md](./docs/guides/MONITORING-GUIDE.md)

❌ WRONG:
[ARCHITECTURE-FLOWS.md](./ARCHITECTURE-FLOWS.md)
[ARCHITECTURE-FLOWS.md](/docs/architecture/ARCHITECTURE-FLOWS.md)
```

### Between Files in Same Directory

```markdown
✅ CORRECT:
[STATUS-REPORT.md](./STATUS-REPORT.md)
[OTHER-DOC.md](./OTHER-DOC.md)
```

### Between Different docs/ Subdirectories

From `docs/reports/` to `docs/architecture/`:
```markdown
✅ CORRECT:
[ARCHITECTURE-FLOWS.md](../architecture/ARCHITECTURE-FLOWS.md)
[MONITORING-GUIDE.md](../guides/MONITORING-GUIDE.md)
```

From `docs/archive/` to `docs/deployment/`:
```markdown
✅ CORRECT:
[BOT-READY.md](../deployment/BOT-READY.md)
```

### From docs/ Subdirectory to Root

From any `docs/` subdirectory to root:
```markdown
✅ CORRECT:
[README.md](../../README.md)
[package.json](../../package.json)
```

## Documentation Directory Mapping

Know where files live:

| Directory | Purpose | Example Files |
|-----------|---------|---------------|
| `docs/architecture/` | Architecture & design | `ARCHITECTURE-FLOWS.md` |
| `docs/deployment/` | Deployment guides | `BOT-READY.md`, `AUTHENTICATION-GUIDE.md` |
| `docs/guides/` | How-to guides | `MONITORING-GUIDE.md` |
| `docs/reports/` | Status reports | `STATUS-REPORT.md`, `FINAL-SUMMARY.md` |
| `docs/cursor/` | Cursor AI rules | `CURSOR-RULES-100-PERCENT.md` |
| `docs/archive/` | Deprecated docs | `BOT-SETUP.md`, `TESTING.md` |

## Link Verification

Before committing markdown changes:

1. **Verify all links work** - Click through to ensure paths are correct
2. **Use relative paths** - Never use absolute filesystem paths
3. **Check moved files** - If you move a markdown file, update all references to it
4. **Test from different locations** - Ensure links work from all referencing files

## External Links

For external resources, use full URLs:

```markdown
✅ CORRECT:
- [Bun Documentation](https://bun.sh/docs)
- [Grammy Framework](https://grammy.dev/)
- [Cloudflare Workers](https://workers.cloudflare.com/)
```

## Images and Assets

If adding images (currently none in project):

```markdown
✅ CORRECT:
![Architecture Diagram](./docs/images/architecture.png)
![Dashboard Screenshot](../images/dashboard.png)
```

## Link Text Best Practices

1. **Use descriptive link text:**
   ```markdown
   ✅ CORRECT: See [Deployment Guide](./docs/deployment/PHASE-2-DEPLOYMENT-GUIDE.md)
   ❌ WRONG: Click [here](./docs/deployment/PHASE-2-DEPLOYMENT-GUIDE.md)
   ```

2. **Include file extension:**
   ```markdown
   ✅ CORRECT: [ARCHITECTURE-FLOWS.md](./docs/architecture/ARCHITECTURE-FLOWS.md)
   ❌ WRONG: [ARCHITECTURE-FLOWS](./docs/architecture/ARCHITECTURE-FLOWS)
   ```

3. **Use consistent formatting:**
   ```markdown
   ✅ CORRECT: **[BOT-READY.md](./docs/deployment/BOT-READY.md)** - Bot configuration
   ```

## When Moving Documentation Files

If you need to move a markdown file:

1. Move the file to new location
2. Search entire codebase for references: `grep -r "OLD-FILENAME.md" .`
3. Update all links in:
   - [README.md](mdc:README.md)
   - Other documentation files
   - Any scripts that reference it
4. Test all updated links

## Common Link Patterns Reference

```markdown
# From README.md to docs/
./docs/architecture/FILE.md
./docs/deployment/FILE.md
./docs/guides/FILE.md
./docs/reports/FILE.md
./docs/archive/FILE.md

# From docs/reports/ to other docs/
../architecture/FILE.md
../deployment/FILE.md
../guides/FILE.md
../archive/FILE.md
./SAME-DIR-FILE.md

# From docs/archive/ to root
../../README.md
../../package.json

# From docs/archive/ to apps/
../../apps/api/wrangler.toml
```
